Course Summary
This course will cover functional and logic programming, concepts of programming language design, 
and formal reasoning about programs and programming languages. The following are the course learning objectives:

Functional Programming (ML/OCaml)
Logic programming
Small-step and large-step operational semantics
Denotational semantics
Fixpoints, fixpoint induction
Axiomatic semantics
Type theory
Untyped and typed lambda calculi
Partial evaluation, non-determinism





